<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Paladin/Necro</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Stupid">Stupid</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:49 p.m. 18/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Paladin/Necro<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1519" TARGET=_self>Paladin/Necro</A> (Wodahs)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> 1) Paladins have the spell Blindness, at level 9. How long does

<BR>&gt; it last ? Is it easy to resist (--> Duels) ?
<P>The first level Shaman spell Flash of Light does the same thing. The duration is tied to the level of the caster, I believe. Higher levels last longer.
<P>&gt; 2) Same question, but for Root, level 22. How long does it last
<BR>&gt; and is it easy to resist ?
<P>Ditto for Root.
<P>&gt; 3) Did anyone of you found NPCs selling high level paladins
<BR>&gt; spells stunning (like Smite or Holy Might of the cleric's
<BR>&gt; spells) ?
<P>No, but I wasn't exactly in Paladin-land either.
<P>&gt; 4) Any infos on the incredible Holy Swords, most powerfull
<BR>&gt; swords of norrath, paladins only ?
<P>There is rumored to be a very powerfull sword that is paladin-only. Soemthing about a drake....
<P>&gt; About Necromancers:
<P>&gt; 1) Did anyone of you found NPCs selling high level that Root ?
<BR>&gt; Or Stun ?
<P>Yes. The Root spell (along with Gate and many others) can be purchased from just about ANY spell merchant. Assuming of course, that you can find a merchant willing to deal with a Necro (many will not).
<P>&gt; I really cannot make up my mind... If you have any tips or ideas
<BR>&gt; about what i should choose, just tell me...
<P>Try both. Alternate characters betweens sessions. Try and keep them at about the same level. Over time, you will naturally gravitate towards one or the other. Play that one. Simple, eh?
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
